OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,367,360,120,260,000,100
PN,36607
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F366A1784812719
OL,3,CGrooming victim makes history after
OL,4,Cconviction quashed
OL,6,FRecounting her relationship with her
OL,7,Fabuser, Ava told ITV News when she was
OL,8,Ftaken into care as a young teenager,
OL,9,Fhe appeared to be the only constant in
OL,10,Fher life.
OL,12,F"He would still come and visit me at
OL,13,Fthe children's home," she recalls.
OL,15,F"He'd still bring me things; phones,
OL,16,Fjewellery, feed me, take me to places,
OL,17,Fhe introduced me to his friends.
OL,19,F"I didn't have my family any more, I'd
OL,20,Fjust become so much more vulnerable.
OL,26,@tD@AOUuD@UO]wD@AOU{D@AOU
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G7/12
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,367,360,120,260,000,100
PN,36608
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F366A1784812719
OL,3,CGrooming victim makes history after
OL,4,Cconviction quashed
OL,6,F"And I think he knew that.
OL,8,F"And it became like a power thing for
OL,9,Fhim, like I would always phone him
OL,10,Fthen - and I would do anything that he
OL,11,Fwanted just to have somebody."
OL,13,FAva says the man would use threats and
OL,14,Fviolence to pressure her into sleeping
OL,15,Fwith other men - some in their 50s.
OL,17,FWhen asked what would happen if she
OL,18,Frefused, she said: "you'd get a slap,
OL,19,Fyou'd get a punch, you'd get called
OL,20,Fall the names under the sun."
OL,26,@nD@AOUpD@AOUsD@^O]zD@TOU|D@]O]
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G8/12
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,367,360,120,260,000,100
PN,36609
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F366A1784812719
OL,3,CGrooming victim makes history after
OL,4,Cconviction quashed
OL,6,FThe man would also use emotional abuse
OL,7,Fby dropping her off at random places
OL,8,Fbefore telling her to make her own way
OL,9,Fback to the children's home.
OL,11,FAva pleaded guilty to the offences,
OL,12,Fbut, since that day, has spent two and
OL,13,Fa half decades trying to clear her
OL,14,Fname.
OL,16,FShe has finally achieved her aim, and
OL,17,Fmade history, after a report
OL,18,Frecommended criminal convictions of
OL,19,Fvictims of child sexual exploitation
OL,20,Fwere reviewed.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G9/12
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,367,360,120,260,000,100
PN,36610
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F366A1784812719
OL,3,CGrooming victim makes history after
OL,4,Cconviction quashed
OL,6,FThe report for the government, by
OL,7,FBaroness Casey in 2025, found where
OL,8,Fvictims were criminalised instead of
OL,9,Fprotected, their convictions should be
OL,10,Fquashed.
OL,12,FIn light of that, Ava's case was put
OL,13,Fforward by the CCRC for appeal, and
OL,14,Fhaving considered the case, the
OL,15,Fprosecution said it did not oppose the
OL,16,Fappeal on two grounds.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}     G10/12
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,367,360,120,260,000,100
PN,36611
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F366A1784812719
OL,3,CGrooming victim makes history after
OL,4,Cconviction quashed
OL,6,FThe first that, due to the passage of
OL,7,Ftime, it was not in a position to
OL,8,Fpresent any evidence or comply with
OL,9,Fits disclosure obligations at any
OL,10,Frehearing.
OL,12,FWhile the second was a decision by the
OL,13,FCrown Prosecution Service (CPS), on
OL,14,Fthe available information, that
OL,15,Fopposing the appeal was not in the
OL,16,Fpublic interest.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}     G11/12
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,367,360,120,260,000,100
PN,36612
SC,0012
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F366A1784812719
OL,3,CGrooming victim makes history after
OL,4,Cconviction quashed
OL,6,FThe CPS said while there was evidence
OL,7,Fthe police and social services were
OL,8,Faware of the danger Ava may have been
OL,9,Fin there was "an absence of evidence"
OL,10,Fif this was considered during the
OL,11,Foriginal criminal proceedings.
OL,13,FIt added that a comment in the court
OL,14,Fextract in relation to the sentence
OL,15,Fwhich said she was "foolishly involved
OL,16,Fwith her boyfriend" does not suggest
OL,17,Fthe case was presented or perceived on
OL,18,Fthe basis she was a child that
OL,19,Frequired protection.
OL,26,@qD@NOUqD@eO]wD@TOUxD@SO]
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}     G12/12
